WEBVTT

1
00:01:39.250 --> 00:01:41.583
Ninety-one, 92...

2
00:01:41.750 --> 00:01:44.250
- It's down there.
- Where? If they catch us--

3
00:01:44.417 --> 00:01:46.417
There's a million bottles
of booze in there.

4
00:01:46.583 --> 00:01:48.125
You think they're gonna miss one?

5
00:02:03.333 --> 00:02:05.458
Weather is with us, sir.

6
00:02:05.792 --> 00:02:09.000
We arrive in port in a couple of hours.

7
00:02:09.167 --> 00:02:10.792
Very good.

8
00:02:10.958 --> 00:02:12.750
You're welcome, sir.

9
00:02:18.083 --> 00:02:21.750
Man, I never smelt anything like this.
Not even when you're in the crapper.

10
00:02:21.917 --> 00:02:25.167
Oh, what, your shit smells like roses?

11
00:02:25.333 --> 00:02:26.667
Hey, look.

12
00:02:27.792 --> 00:02:29.667
I'll give you a hand.

13
00:02:35.833 --> 00:02:39.333
- Thought you said it was booze.
- That's what the papers said.

14
00:02:44.292 --> 00:02:46.500
Captain, we have a breach
in lower level. Look.

15
00:02:46.667 --> 00:02:48.292
- Which section?
- 101.

16
00:02:49.125 --> 00:02:50.458
Fuck. Take the wheel.

17
00:02:50.625 --> 00:02:52.042
- Yes, sir.
- Fuck.

18
00:02:54.083 --> 00:02:56.333
Close the door! Get the masks.

19
00:03:02.500 --> 00:03:04.667
Holy shit.

20
00:03:05.333 --> 00:03:07.333
Take care of them.

21
00:03:51.750 --> 00:03:53.500
- Morning.
- Passport, please.

22
00:04:00.125 --> 00:04:01.167
Rough seas?

23
00:04:01.709 --> 00:04:05.000
The sea was smooth. The party was
a bit rough, if you know what I mean.

24
00:04:05.167 --> 00:04:06.750
- Ibiza.
- Yeah.

25
00:04:06.917 --> 00:04:08.375
Thanks.

26
00:04:18.959 --> 00:04:21.792
When I was a kid,
my father used to take me fishing.

27
00:04:21.959 --> 00:04:25.209
Never could figure out how he knew
where the fish were.

28
00:04:26.334 --> 00:04:29.792
They were always exactly
where he said they would be.

29
00:04:54.542 --> 00:04:55.917
Security check.

30
00:04:56.292 --> 00:04:57.917
Do I look like a security risk?

31
00:04:58.167 --> 00:05:01.250
Please step out of the car and bring
your documents to the office.

32
00:05:02.084 --> 00:05:03.667
My documents are right here, sir.

33
00:05:03.834 --> 00:05:06.000
The computer is in the office.

34
00:05:07.500 --> 00:05:08.750
Her too.

35
00:05:08.917 --> 00:05:10.625
She's sleeping.

36
00:05:10.792 --> 00:05:13.584
- With her documents.
- Okay, sure.

37
00:05:28.459 --> 00:05:29.625
You're gonna lose it.

38
00:05:34.084 --> 00:05:35.834
Close, inspector, you're close.

39
00:05:40.625 --> 00:05:42.625
That's a big one. Go left, go left.

40
00:05:45.167 --> 00:05:47.000
Don't let him get away.

41
00:05:51.625 --> 00:05:52.917
You're close.

42
00:05:58.250 --> 00:05:59.792
Go left, go left! Go right!

43
00:06:03.500 --> 00:06:05.667
Must be Moby Dick you hooked.
Need some help?

44
00:06:05.834 --> 00:06:06.959
No, thank you, Frank.

45
00:06:08.250 --> 00:06:11.500
I have been fishing these waters
since before you were born.

46
00:06:16.834 --> 00:06:20.292
You were close, inspector.
You were close.

47
00:06:23.834 --> 00:06:27.500
Good thing that we French have such
a highly developed sense of humor.

48
00:06:27.834 --> 00:06:31.250
With all due respect, the French
think Jerry Lewis is a genius.

49
00:06:31.417 --> 00:06:34.584
- Jerry Lewis is a genius.
- Dean was the genius.

50
00:06:34.750 --> 00:06:37.834
No, Dean just stood there
with a drink and a cigarette.

51
00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:41.000
My point exactly.
Anyone can fall down and get a laugh.

52
00:06:41.167 --> 00:06:44.459
How many people can do it standing
still with a drink and a cigarette?

53
00:06:55.417 --> 00:06:59.167
I am afraid our day of leisure
is cut short.

54
00:06:59.334 --> 00:07:00.834
There is a mess in Marseilles.

55
00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:03.917
Some madman driving an Audi
at impossible speeds.

56
00:07:06.459 --> 00:07:08.375
Don't look at me.

57
00:07:08.542 --> 00:07:11.459
That is the first place
the chief told me to look.

58
00:07:11.625 --> 00:07:15.834
But I will tell him
you have the perfect alibi.

59
00:07:17.334 --> 00:07:19.209
As usual.

60
00:07:24.834 --> 00:07:26.125
Tarconi!

61
00:07:27.459 --> 00:07:28.917
- Please!
- I am sorry, Frank.

62
00:07:29.084 --> 00:07:32.209
- It's our first bite!
- Yeah, yeah.

63
00:07:32.917 --> 00:07:34.834
- Please.
- Yeah.

64
00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:36.500
Stop the boat. Come on.

65
00:07:36.667 --> 00:07:39.417
- No. No, Frank.
- Come on, please.

66
00:08:19.584 --> 00:08:23.167
Purpose of your visit, Mr. Johnson?

67
00:08:23.917 --> 00:08:24.959
Business.

68
00:08:25.500 --> 00:08:26.750
What kind of business?

69
00:08:27.334 --> 00:08:29.167
Environmental protection.

70
00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:37.167
Thank you.

71
00:08:39.459 --> 00:08:42.834
Mr. Minister, you're giving the opening
address at an EU conference...

72
00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:45.750
...on environmental impact of industry
in Odessa tomorrow.

73
00:08:45.917 --> 00:08:48.667
- What is top on your list of priorities?
- It's a short list.

74
00:08:48.834 --> 00:08:51.625
There's one item: the environment
and how to protect it.

75
00:08:51.792 --> 00:08:53.625
In the face of increasing pressure...

76
00:08:53.792 --> 00:08:56.750
...for industries to compete
successfully in a global economy...

77
00:08:56.917 --> 00:09:00.292
...that goal can sometimes come up
against some very harsh realities.

78
00:09:00.459 --> 00:09:03.459
Well, not as harsh as
a polluted and uninhabitable planet.

79
00:09:03.625 --> 00:09:05.334
Gentlemen, if you'll excuse me now...

80
00:09:05.500 --> 00:09:08.750
...I have trees to save
and industrialists to disappoint.

81
00:09:12.417 --> 00:09:14.667
- Your speech for tomorrow.
- Any good?

82
00:09:15.167 --> 00:09:19.042
- It's going to piss off a lot of people.
- Excellent.

83
00:09:42.125 --> 00:09:43.167
Hello?

84
00:09:44.334 --> 00:09:46.125
Mr. Minister?

85
00:09:47.125 --> 00:09:48.167
Who is this?

86
00:09:48.500 --> 00:09:50.834
My name is not important.

87
00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:53.292
I've been put in charge of
the negotiations...

88
00:09:53.459 --> 00:09:55.875
...you are engaged in with Ecocorp...

89
00:09:56.042 --> 00:09:59.334
...for issuance of their license
to do business in the Ukraine.

90
00:09:59.500 --> 00:10:02.000
You must be misinformed,
Mr. Whatever-Your-Name-Is.

91
00:10:02.167 --> 00:10:04.292
I've terminated negotiations permanently.

92
00:10:04.459 --> 00:10:06.875
I think you will reconsider
that position...

93
00:10:07.042 --> 00:10:10.500
...once you have a chance to study
the documents in the envelope.

94
00:10:25.334 --> 00:10:27.334
I'll be in touch.

95
00:11:08.584 --> 00:11:10.917
Yeah, there's been an accident.

96
00:11:11.251 --> 00:11:14.626
Send an ambulance,
8 Route de la Falaise.

97
00:11:33.001 --> 00:11:34.417
Malcolm.

98
00:11:34.584 --> 00:11:36.292
Malcolm. Malcolm.

99
00:11:42.376 --> 00:11:44.834
I asked you for your price.
What is this?

100
00:11:45.001 --> 00:11:49.126
A man who might be interested
in taking the job. This man will.

101
00:11:49.626 --> 00:11:51.501
My boss said you're the man for the job.

102
00:11:51.667 --> 00:11:53.334
Your boss got his facts wrong.

103
00:11:55.709 --> 00:11:57.751
Two things you should know about my boss:

104
00:11:57.917 --> 00:12:01.167
He never gets his facts wrong,
he never takes no for an answer.

105
00:12:01.334 --> 00:12:03.417
Well, there's a first time for everything.

106
00:12:12.001 --> 00:12:15.126
Well, not this time.

107
00:12:21.334 --> 00:12:23.417
You don't wanna do this.

108
00:12:23.584 --> 00:12:27.542
I don't think you're in a position to
tell me what I do and don't wanna do.

109
00:12:27.709 --> 00:12:30.709
You have 10 seconds to change your mind.

110
00:12:35.084 --> 00:12:38.501
I'll give you five seconds
to remove your hand.

111
00:13:38.292 --> 00:13:40.417
Malcolm. Malcolm.

112
00:13:40.584 --> 00:13:41.626
You hear me?

113
00:13:44.251 --> 00:13:46.626
Mal, I said drop in anytime,
but I didn't mean...

114
00:13:46.959 --> 00:13:49.667
- Nowhere else to go.
- Just take it easy, okay?

115
00:13:51.334 --> 00:13:52.626
Don't move me from the car.

116
00:13:52.792 --> 00:13:56.792
- It's just till the ambulance arrives.
- No ambulance.

117
00:13:57.626 --> 00:14:00.584
You need a doctor, you've been shot.
I can't take care of this.

118
00:14:02.459 --> 00:14:04.959
Not far from car.

119
00:14:06.417 --> 00:14:07.501
Relax.

120
00:14:07.834 --> 00:14:12.501
Just try to stay calm.
We'll have you fixed up in no time.

121
00:14:23.501 --> 00:14:25.542
He's inside. Quick, it's serious.

122
00:14:30.084 --> 00:14:31.126
Sir?

123
00:14:31.292 --> 00:14:34.501
- You wanna be careful moving him.
- We know our job, okay?

124
00:14:34.667 --> 00:14:37.209
Sir, can you hear me?

125
00:14:37.376 --> 00:14:38.959
This car... No...

126
00:14:39.126 --> 00:14:40.667
If you hear me, press my hand.

127
00:14:41.084 --> 00:14:42.417
The car...

128
00:15:32.501 --> 00:15:34.501
Am I in heaven?

129
00:15:35.209 --> 00:15:37.167
Actually, you're in a bit of the shit.

130
00:15:37.834 --> 00:15:40.334
You'll help me out of it?

131
00:15:41.001 --> 00:15:42.792
That depends on how deep you're in.

132
00:15:43.126 --> 00:15:46.292
- Don't trust anyone.
- Couldn't agree with you more.

133
00:15:48.501 --> 00:15:50.084
- Come on.
- No! Don't leave the car!

134
00:15:50.251 --> 00:15:53.459
- What's so special about the car?
- Not the car.

135
00:16:05.584 --> 00:16:07.417
Wait!

136
00:16:36.167 --> 00:16:37.167
I told you.

137
00:16:42.292 --> 00:16:44.084
<i>Don't trust anyone.</i>

138
00:16:45.667 --> 00:16:47.167
<i>I told you.</i>

139
00:17:39.626 --> 00:17:41.793
I took the liberty of bringing your suit.

140
00:17:41.959 --> 00:17:44.168
It's what you wear when
you're working, correct?

141
00:17:44.334 --> 00:17:47.001
Correct. But I'm not working.

142
00:17:47.501 --> 00:17:50.668
- You see, boss? I told you.
- Please, Joseph.

143
00:17:51.334 --> 00:17:55.334
Your approach was not very effective in
presenting our proposal the first time.

144
00:17:55.501 --> 00:17:57.084
Thank you.

145
00:17:57.709 --> 00:17:58.751
As I was saying...

146
00:17:58.918 --> 00:18:02.084
...we came to you in good faith.
You said you were unavailable.

147
00:18:02.251 --> 00:18:04.709
We contracted with the man
whose number you gave us.

148
00:18:04.876 --> 00:18:06.459
He proved to be ineffective.

149
00:18:06.626 --> 00:18:09.918
And now I am left with unfinished business.

150
00:18:10.084 --> 00:18:12.418
The way I see it, you're responsible.

151
00:18:12.876 --> 00:18:14.959
I understand your point of view.

152
00:18:15.126 --> 00:18:16.334
But I'm still unavailable.

153
00:18:18.334 --> 00:18:19.834
Boss, can I say something?

154
00:18:22.626 --> 00:18:24.876
Anyone else wanna say something?

155
00:18:28.001 --> 00:18:29.543
Good.

156
00:18:29.793 --> 00:18:31.834
Find me a smarter one.

157
00:18:34.168 --> 00:18:36.209
You have three seconds
to change your mind...

158
00:18:36.376 --> 00:18:39.168
...or you're gonna
be permanently unavailable.

159
00:18:39.793 --> 00:18:41.376
One.

160
00:18:43.626 --> 00:18:44.668
Two.

161
00:18:47.834 --> 00:18:48.959
One condition.

162
00:18:52.043 --> 00:18:53.584
I'm listening.

163
00:18:54.251 --> 00:18:56.501
I drive my own car.

164
00:18:57.751 --> 00:18:59.251
Deal.

165
00:19:02.501 --> 00:19:05.959
In anticipation of your answer, we took
the liberty of bringing your car.

166
00:19:06.126 --> 00:19:10.084
Changed the oil, gave it a tune-up,
took out all the non-essential material.

167
00:19:10.251 --> 00:19:13.834
Left the switch-over license plates.
Love that.

168
00:19:14.001 --> 00:19:16.293
Replaced the GPS with one of our own.

169
00:19:16.459 --> 00:19:18.334
Preprogrammed.
More efficient that way.

170
00:19:18.751 --> 00:19:22.793
Why I was so insistent on using only
the best man for this assignment?

171
00:19:25.501 --> 00:19:27.959
We're playing in a much larger game here.

172
00:19:28.126 --> 00:19:32.834
Don't think of this as just another job.
Think of it as a mission.

173
00:19:34.834 --> 00:19:37.668
I'm so pleased to find we share
the same approach to our work.

174
00:19:37.834 --> 00:19:39.959
I make a deal, that's the deal.
Just like you.

175
00:19:40.126 --> 00:19:42.876
You don't like names. Neither do I.
We're both precise.

176
00:19:43.043 --> 00:19:46.168
Neither one of us has any interest
in what we're paid to do...

177
00:19:46.334 --> 00:19:50.334
...beyond what we are paid to do.
Those are your rules, right?

178
00:19:58.501 --> 00:20:00.168
You forgot one.

179
00:20:00.709 --> 00:20:03.668
- I work alone.
- I thought you might like the company.

180
00:20:04.084 --> 00:20:06.418
Thought you wanted me
to complete a mission.

181
00:20:08.626 --> 00:20:10.459
You're right. I do.

182
00:20:13.168 --> 00:20:14.418
Wait.

183
00:20:16.293 --> 00:20:18.251
What, you wanna change the rules?

184
00:20:19.834 --> 00:20:22.626
Every rule has an exception.
Let's make one for today.

185
00:20:25.834 --> 00:20:27.001
You're the boss.

186
00:20:29.751 --> 00:20:31.793
Anything else?

187
00:20:32.418 --> 00:20:34.251
The jewelry.
Anything I should know?

188
00:20:37.876 --> 00:20:40.543
You remember those jokers
trying to blow up airliners...

189
00:20:40.709 --> 00:20:43.584
...by sneaking liquids through
and combining them onboard?

190
00:20:43.751 --> 00:20:45.668
Same principle, just refined.

191
00:20:45.834 --> 00:20:47.584
Twenty-five feet from the car...

192
00:20:47.751 --> 00:20:51.168
...yellow light comes on,
signaling the first liquid is ready.

193
00:20:51.334 --> 00:20:53.168
Fifty feet, orange.

194
00:20:53.959 --> 00:20:55.709
Second liquid flows into the chamber.

195
00:20:55.876 --> 00:20:58.876
Seventy-five feet,
you're gonna see red.

196
00:21:04.084 --> 00:21:05.876
Time to go.

197
00:21:06.334 --> 00:21:10.084
This phone is programmed
to call only one number, mine.

198
00:21:11.126 --> 00:21:15.001
When you pass the first toll on the
road going north, call me, all right?

199
00:21:16.084 --> 00:21:19.084
Money for gas and food.

200
00:21:19.251 --> 00:21:20.501
Any other questions?

201
00:21:52.043 --> 00:21:54.251
Would you mind buckling your seat belt?

202
00:22:05.126 --> 00:22:08.334
Don't suppose you wanna tell me
what this is all about?

203
00:22:14.084 --> 00:22:16.001
Great.

204
00:22:31.668 --> 00:22:34.293
<i>Ocean Pearl
requesting cargo clearance.</i>

205
00:22:35.959 --> 00:22:38.501
The papers are with
the environmental agency.

206
00:22:38.834 --> 00:22:40.793
Drop anchor and wait to dock.

207
00:22:40.959 --> 00:22:43.626
<i>- We'll inform you when they're signed.
- Okay.</i>

208
00:22:53.168 --> 00:22:54.876
I know what happened to you.

209
00:22:55.043 --> 00:22:57.334
But what happened to Frank?

210
00:23:03.001 --> 00:23:07.168
Colonel Medved over at Intelligence
has been given all the information.

211
00:23:07.793 --> 00:23:09.168
He knows it's top priority.

212
00:23:09.334 --> 00:23:11.918
He wants you to know
he has his best men on it.

213
00:23:12.084 --> 00:23:14.293
He'll keep it out of official channels.

214
00:23:14.459 --> 00:23:18.168
He suggests you buy
as much time as you can.

215
00:24:13.501 --> 00:24:18.251
Look, I don't know what your part in all
this is or isn't. And I don't really care.

216
00:24:18.418 --> 00:24:20.751
You were here first,
you know more than I do...

217
00:24:20.918 --> 00:24:22.668
...download me on what you know.

218
00:24:22.834 --> 00:24:24.418
I know nothing.

219
00:24:24.584 --> 00:24:26.834
How did you know Malcolm?

220
00:24:27.209 --> 00:24:28.251
I didn't.

221
00:24:28.793 --> 00:24:31.668
You just happened to end up in a car
with a man you don't know?

222
00:24:33.835 --> 00:24:35.960
I'm now in a car with man I don't know.

223
00:24:37.793 --> 00:24:40.460
Aren't you supposed to make a call?

224
00:24:46.793 --> 00:24:48.293
<i>Nice to hear from you.</i>

225
00:24:48.460 --> 00:24:51.543
You can skip the pleasantries.
Just give me the code.

226
00:24:51.835 --> 00:24:53.501
<i>1-1-2-6.</i>

227
00:24:57.710 --> 00:25:00.168
<i>Call me when you arrive.</i>

228
00:25:01.918 --> 00:25:04.335
What's in Budapest?

229
00:25:04.501 --> 00:25:06.793
Goulash. Beer.

230
00:25:13.751 --> 00:25:15.001
All right.

231
00:25:15.168 --> 00:25:18.001
Let's rewind here,
start with the proper introductions.

232
00:25:18.626 --> 00:25:21.168
What happened to the rule of no names?

233
00:25:21.335 --> 00:25:24.460
I'm suspending that rule for the moment.

234
00:25:27.501 --> 00:25:29.710
I'm Frank Martin.

235
00:25:32.001 --> 00:25:33.460
And your name is?

236
00:25:36.626 --> 00:25:39.001
What matters, my name?

237
00:25:39.585 --> 00:25:42.501
Well, we're in this situation together.

238
00:25:43.043 --> 00:25:44.626
No.

239
00:25:47.251 --> 00:25:51.001
We're sitting here with two exploding
bracelets on, going to the same place.

240
00:25:52.168 --> 00:25:54.126
I'd call that being in the same situation.

241
00:25:54.543 --> 00:25:57.168
It's not. They are going to kill you.

242
00:25:59.126 --> 00:26:01.168
I'm aware of that.

243
00:26:02.085 --> 00:26:05.126
In all probability, after they kill me,
you're next on the list.

244
00:26:05.293 --> 00:26:08.835
Now, if I'm gonna keep that from
happening, I'm gonna need a little help.

245
00:26:09.001 --> 00:26:11.668
From the top. We have this problem.

246
00:26:11.835 --> 00:26:13.835
You think I don't know it's a problem?

247
00:26:14.293 --> 00:26:16.168
I look stupid to you?

248
00:26:16.835 --> 00:26:19.376
I didn't say you were stupid.

249
00:26:21.085 --> 00:26:22.501
But we have a problem...

250
00:26:22.668 --> 00:26:26.335
...and you're not being very helpful
in participating in the solution of it.

251
00:26:28.001 --> 00:26:30.293
I don't want to talk anymore.

252
00:26:37.626 --> 00:26:38.918
Fine.

253
00:26:52.251 --> 00:26:54.001
What did you say your name was?

254
00:26:54.960 --> 00:26:57.960
Frank. Frank Martin.

255
00:26:58.918 --> 00:27:01.085
Frank Martin.

256
00:27:01.418 --> 00:27:03.501
Valentina.

257
00:27:06.501 --> 00:27:09.043
Pleased to meet you.

258
00:28:04.960 --> 00:28:07.168
<i>The gentlemen
from Ecocorp are here.</i>

259
00:28:08.585 --> 00:28:09.793
Show them in.

260
00:28:17.543 --> 00:28:18.585
Gentlemen.

261
00:28:21.835 --> 00:28:23.376
Mr. Minister.

262
00:28:23.543 --> 00:28:26.460
We'd like to thank you for
reconsidering our proposal...

263
00:28:26.626 --> 00:28:29.585
- ...on such short notice.
- You make it very hard not to.

264
00:28:29.751 --> 00:28:33.418
Well, yes. We do have a reputation
of not taking no for an answer.

265
00:28:34.335 --> 00:28:35.835
Here are the contracts.

266
00:28:37.668 --> 00:28:38.751
All in order.

267
00:28:39.543 --> 00:28:41.626
We were told the ships
couldn't be cleared...

268
00:28:41.793 --> 00:28:43.835
...unless you personally
signed off on them.

269
00:28:44.001 --> 00:28:45.335
Ships?

270
00:28:45.876 --> 00:28:47.335
I thought there was only one.

271
00:28:47.501 --> 00:28:50.001
Oh, well, here's the thing.

272
00:28:50.168 --> 00:28:52.960
In order to make the venture
more profitable...

273
00:28:53.126 --> 00:28:56.126
...we need to process the material
in a volume that makes sense.

274
00:28:56.293 --> 00:28:57.960
How many ships are we talking about?

275
00:28:58.126 --> 00:29:01.918
Plus the one in the port
waiting on clearance, eight.

276
00:29:02.501 --> 00:29:03.751
Eight.

277
00:29:04.085 --> 00:29:05.293
This year.

278
00:29:06.501 --> 00:29:09.585
Protecting the environment
is a long-term commitment.

279
00:29:09.751 --> 00:29:11.793
You've said so yourself, haven't you?

280
00:29:11.960 --> 00:29:14.501
And I will do again tomorrow in Odessa...

281
00:29:14.668 --> 00:29:17.585
...where I will sign these.

282
00:29:18.501 --> 00:29:21.335
We were really hoping to settle this today.

283
00:29:21.501 --> 00:29:25.876
I want to review them, now that
there are some addendums.

284
00:29:26.043 --> 00:29:28.251
Twenty-four hours
doesn't make a difference...

285
00:29:28.418 --> 00:29:30.835
...on such a long-term
commitment, will it?

286
00:29:31.543 --> 00:29:34.293
No, of course not.

287
00:29:34.460 --> 00:29:38.501
Then I will see you tomorrow
in Odessa. Let's say 9 a.m.

288
00:29:44.335 --> 00:29:45.751
<i>Yes.</i>

289
00:29:45.918 --> 00:29:47.668
Okay, I'll stay.

290
00:29:47.835 --> 00:29:49.501
<i>- But the material is leaking.
- And?</i>

291
00:29:49.668 --> 00:29:52.293
<i>- We won't be able to hide it.
- I'll take care of it.</i>

292
00:29:52.460 --> 00:29:53.793
If ever they check...

293
00:29:53.960 --> 00:29:56.293
<i>Easy. The deal will be closed
very soon.</i>

294
00:29:56.460 --> 00:29:58.126
Twenty-four hours. No more.

295
00:30:07.168 --> 00:30:11.001
- Yes?
- I've bought you another 24 hours.

296
00:30:11.168 --> 00:30:13.501
You have until tomorrow, 9 a.m.

297
00:30:13.668 --> 00:30:15.501
That should be more than enough time.

298
00:30:16.085 --> 00:30:17.960
<i>Do you have a lead?</i>

299
00:30:18.126 --> 00:30:19.960
Better than a lead.

300
00:30:20.751 --> 00:30:21.793
A location.

301
00:31:00.293 --> 00:31:02.293
I'm hungry.

302
00:31:03.293 --> 00:31:05.835
We're 100 kilometers from beer and sausage.

303
00:31:07.251 --> 00:31:09.668
I don't like sausage.

304
00:31:12.460 --> 00:31:14.418
What would you like?

305
00:31:18.543 --> 00:31:20.210
Veal.

306
00:31:20.376 --> 00:31:22.335
Roast, with carrots...

307
00:31:22.501 --> 00:31:23.960
...and beets.

308
00:31:25.501 --> 00:31:28.585
In gravy, with Madeira in stock.

309
00:31:28.752 --> 00:31:30.043
Nothing to start?

310
00:31:33.585 --> 00:31:35.585
A salad.

311
00:31:36.168 --> 00:31:39.460
Greens tossed with balsamic.

312
00:31:39.627 --> 00:31:41.418
From Modena.

313
00:31:41.585 --> 00:31:43.002
Aged?

314
00:31:43.168 --> 00:31:45.168
Of course, aged.

315
00:31:48.168 --> 00:31:50.210
And for dessert?

316
00:31:51.460 --> 00:31:53.085
Sachertorte.

317
00:31:53.585 --> 00:31:56.127
With whipped cream or without?

318
00:31:57.460 --> 00:31:58.835
With.

319
00:31:59.585 --> 00:32:01.460
To drink?

320
00:32:03.335 --> 00:32:04.585
Wine.

321
00:32:04.752 --> 00:32:06.585
Tokaj, perhaps?

322
00:32:07.085 --> 00:32:08.168
Ice wine.

323
00:32:09.335 --> 00:32:11.168
Of course.

324
00:32:23.002 --> 00:32:25.835
- What are you doing?
- Seeing a man about some jewelry.

325
00:32:37.502 --> 00:32:39.085
He's gone off the reservation.

326
00:32:41.418 --> 00:32:44.752
Send someone to get him back on.

327
00:32:45.377 --> 00:32:47.335
Don't kill him.

328
00:33:14.002 --> 00:33:16.668
<i>Frank. It's so good to see you,
mein Freund.</i>

329
00:33:16.918 --> 00:33:19.252
Good to see you too, Otto.

330
00:33:19.585 --> 00:33:22.127
You didn't mention you bring company.

331
00:33:22.627 --> 00:33:23.793
It's not really company.

332
00:33:24.293 --> 00:33:25.960
It's...

333
00:33:27.127 --> 00:33:28.252
...complicated.

334
00:33:28.418 --> 00:33:31.418
With you, it's always complicated.
You can tell me about it...

335
00:33:31.585 --> 00:33:35.335
<i>...over a nice schnitzel
with Kartoffelsalat I have prepared.</i>

336
00:33:35.960 --> 00:33:38.168
Hey, Otto, you know
I love your schnitzel...

337
00:33:38.335 --> 00:33:40.793
...but we need to get rid of this first.

338
00:33:43.293 --> 00:33:46.793
Binary free-form
magnetic-resolution technology.

339
00:33:47.252 --> 00:33:48.502
English, please, Otto.

340
00:33:49.918 --> 00:33:51.960
There's a program the
Pentagon has funded...

341
00:33:52.127 --> 00:33:55.252
...through one of their
subsidiary front companies...

342
00:33:55.418 --> 00:33:58.793
...that's been experimenting with
this new kind of weaponry...

343
00:33:58.960 --> 00:34:01.627
...based on the theory
of magnetic attraction.

344
00:34:01.793 --> 00:34:03.835
Very hush-hush stuff.

345
00:34:05.502 --> 00:34:08.418
I didn't realize you were in the loop
on the Pentagon hush-hush.

346
00:34:08.585 --> 00:34:10.668
You wouldn't believe
what you can discover...

347
00:34:10.835 --> 00:34:13.002
...walking through the Internet.

348
00:34:13.168 --> 00:34:15.460
You wanna see the invasion plans for Iran?

349
00:34:15.877 --> 00:34:17.668
Maybe some other time.

350
00:34:17.835 --> 00:34:21.293
Right now we need to get this thing off
without blowing myself to Iran.

351
00:34:21.460 --> 00:34:23.918
I don't wanna bother you
with the details...

352
00:34:24.085 --> 00:34:28.668
...but usually there's
a transmitter plate close by.

353
00:34:34.835 --> 00:34:36.335
You should not be doing this.

354
00:34:36.502 --> 00:34:38.502
First you don't talk,
now you offer advice.

355
00:34:38.668 --> 00:34:41.168
Not advice. A warning.

356
00:34:41.752 --> 00:34:43.293
Well, a little late for warnings,
don't you think?

357
00:34:50.335 --> 00:34:51.502
I agree with you.

358
00:34:56.085 --> 00:34:57.668
You're off course.

359
00:35:03.752 --> 00:35:06.377
- Should I?
- Yeah, you should.

360
00:35:12.335 --> 00:35:13.960
Look, fellas...

361
00:35:14.752 --> 00:35:17.668
...some things in the car
were a bit off, needed checking.

362
00:35:19.085 --> 00:35:21.418
In my profession,
a man is only as good as the car.

363
00:35:21.585 --> 00:35:24.835
You take care of the car,
the car will take care of you.

364
00:35:26.960 --> 00:35:29.335
The boss says, "Back on the road."

365
00:35:29.793 --> 00:35:31.168
Frank?

366
00:35:31.918 --> 00:35:32.960
Keep at it.

367
00:35:35.668 --> 00:35:36.835
Back in the car, Frank.

368
00:35:37.502 --> 00:35:38.710
No.

369
00:36:50.002 --> 00:36:52.127
- Find it?
- Not yet.

370
00:38:08.752 --> 00:38:10.377
You're the smart one?

371
00:38:10.543 --> 00:38:13.168
No. I'm the big one.

372
00:39:05.294 --> 00:39:06.627
Not so big anymore, are you?

373
00:39:29.169 --> 00:39:31.002
Found it.

374
00:39:35.210 --> 00:39:37.752
- The transmitter.
- Can you remove it?

375
00:39:40.210 --> 00:39:41.252
It's wired.

376
00:39:41.752 --> 00:39:43.585
If I do:

377
00:40:41.460 --> 00:40:43.502
You fight good.

378
00:40:46.502 --> 00:40:48.669
But you tie bad.

379
00:40:54.252 --> 00:40:55.294
Where are you going?

380
00:40:55.794 --> 00:40:57.585
Tired.

381
00:40:58.752 --> 00:41:01.002
That's why I prefer to deal with cars.

382
00:41:01.835 --> 00:41:03.502
That makes two of us.

383
00:41:04.002 --> 00:41:07.002
What do you want me to do
when they--? When they wake up?

384
00:41:07.169 --> 00:41:10.294
Probably best to take
the rest of the day off.

385
00:41:28.585 --> 00:41:29.752
I'm not amused.

386
00:41:29.919 --> 00:41:31.835
You'd be less amused if you ended up dead.

387
00:41:32.002 --> 00:41:34.419
<i>If you wanted me dead, I'd be dead.
You need me.</i>

388
00:41:34.585 --> 00:41:37.419
You want me to complete the job,
I need some clarification.

389
00:41:39.002 --> 00:41:40.169
I'm listening.

390
00:41:40.585 --> 00:41:41.752
In person.

391
00:41:41.919 --> 00:41:43.377
We've already done in person.

392
00:41:43.544 --> 00:41:45.669
<i>Well, not to my satisfaction,
apparently.</i>

393
00:41:46.377 --> 00:41:49.335
Right now, my satisfaction
should be your main concern.

394
00:41:50.377 --> 00:41:52.960
Same place. One hour.
Wait for my call.

395
00:42:49.752 --> 00:42:50.835
Hello?

396
00:42:51.002 --> 00:42:53.002
You've disappointed me.

397
00:42:53.169 --> 00:42:56.252
You won't be the first
and you won't be the last.

398
00:42:56.419 --> 00:43:01.210
- I told you I wanted to do this in person.
- That won't be necessary. You see...

399
00:43:01.377 --> 00:43:03.502
...since our little chat
at the beginning...

400
00:43:03.669 --> 00:43:07.169
...I've been thinking I don't need
the best for this mundane assignment.

401
00:43:07.335 --> 00:43:09.544
Any idiot with a driver's license will do.

402
00:43:09.710 --> 00:43:12.794
So in the words of the
great American, Donald Trump:

403
00:43:12.960 --> 00:43:16.335
I'm sorry, but you're fired.

404
00:44:02.585 --> 00:44:03.669
Who are you?

405
00:44:04.002 --> 00:44:06.669
- Your new chauffeur.
- I want the old one back.

406
00:44:06.835 --> 00:44:09.169
He's about to go to pieces.

407
00:45:17.544 --> 00:45:18.919
You're fired.

408
00:45:22.710 --> 00:45:23.794
How was your nap?

409
00:45:24.127 --> 00:45:26.544
Restful. How was your phone call?

410
00:45:26.711 --> 00:45:29.211
Brief. Fasten your seat belt.

411
00:45:41.086 --> 00:45:42.127
Tarconi.

412
00:45:42.294 --> 00:45:43.336
It's me.

413
00:45:44.502 --> 00:45:46.252
I was wondering when you would call.

414
00:45:46.419 --> 00:45:47.669
I've been busy.

415
00:45:47.836 --> 00:45:50.502
Let me guess. In Budapest?

416
00:45:51.711 --> 00:45:53.086
You've been busy too.

417
00:45:53.544 --> 00:45:56.419
Never a problem keeping that way
with a friend like you.

418
00:45:56.586 --> 00:45:59.461
So I don't have to be redundant,
tell me what you know.

419
00:45:59.627 --> 00:46:02.086
There is a black Mercedes also in Budapest.

420
00:46:02.252 --> 00:46:04.336
<i>Probably not occupied
by friends of yours.</i>

421
00:46:04.502 --> 00:46:07.169
That is what I know.
Now tell me what you know.

422
00:46:07.961 --> 00:46:11.336
I have two bags in the back
and a girl in the front.

423
00:46:11.502 --> 00:46:13.419
Russian, I think.

424
00:46:13.627 --> 00:46:15.836
I don't know what she
has to do with anything.

425
00:46:16.002 --> 00:46:18.002
Have you tried asking her?

426
00:46:18.169 --> 00:46:20.252
<i>- Now, why didn't I think of that?
- Sorry.</i>

427
00:46:20.419 --> 00:46:22.169
Of course you've asked.
And she says?

428
00:46:22.752 --> 00:46:24.086
I'm going to die.

429
00:46:24.252 --> 00:46:26.586
Typical. Russians.

430
00:46:26.752 --> 00:46:29.002
They are so dark.

431
00:46:29.169 --> 00:46:32.669
I remember, in school,
reading Dostoyevsky and thinking...

432
00:46:32.836 --> 00:46:35.544
...when do these people laugh?

433
00:46:35.711 --> 00:46:37.419
One page after the other...

434
00:46:37.586 --> 00:46:40.586
...misery and suffering
like you wouldn't believe, Frank.

435
00:46:40.752 --> 00:46:44.169
Inspector, can we save the
literature lesson? I'm blinking here.

436
00:46:44.336 --> 00:46:45.586
Is that code?

437
00:46:46.502 --> 00:46:49.961
No, it's some bracelet
they accessorized us with.

438
00:46:50.127 --> 00:46:52.377
Wired to explode
if we get too far from the car.

439
00:46:52.544 --> 00:46:53.586
<i>They?</i>

440
00:46:54.252 --> 00:46:55.336
Some American.

441
00:46:55.502 --> 00:46:58.377
<i>Can you be more specific?
A name? A number?</i>

442
00:46:58.544 --> 00:46:59.627
Nothing.

443
00:46:59.794 --> 00:47:02.002
Why do you always make it so easy, Frank?

444
00:47:02.169 --> 00:47:03.919
It's my nature.

445
00:47:04.086 --> 00:47:05.961
<i>Where are you? I will come there.</i>

446
00:47:06.127 --> 00:47:08.627
That's not a good idea.
They have me on a short leash.

447
00:47:08.794 --> 00:47:11.669
I can't be of much help
if you do not give me something.

448
00:47:13.252 --> 00:47:15.419
How close are you to a computer?

449
00:47:19.211 --> 00:47:20.336
Yes, Frank?

450
00:47:20.502 --> 00:47:23.336
<i>That wasn't very nice,
back there in the market.</i>

451
00:47:23.502 --> 00:47:26.336
You were the one
who broke the rules, not me.

452
00:47:26.502 --> 00:47:28.627
<i>Point well taken.</i>

453
00:47:28.836 --> 00:47:32.419
That makes us even. What say
we start with a clean slate?

454
00:47:32.586 --> 00:47:35.752
So this call is about
kiss-and-make-up, then?

455
00:47:36.336 --> 00:47:37.461
<i>More or less.</i>

456
00:47:37.627 --> 00:47:40.544
You have what I need
to get the bracelet off...

457
00:47:40.711 --> 00:47:43.586
...I have the packages
you need delivered.

458
00:47:44.586 --> 00:47:47.169
Here are the new coordinates,
then: 2-6-12.

459
00:47:47.502 --> 00:47:49.002
<i>That'll take you to the place...</i>

460
00:47:49.169 --> 00:47:51.502
<i>...where we can have a
conclusion to this business.</i>

461
00:47:51.669 --> 00:47:53.461
I look forward to it.

462
00:47:59.419 --> 00:48:00.752
Frank.

463
00:48:00.919 --> 00:48:02.169
<i>Did you get it?</i>

464
00:48:07.127 --> 00:48:09.086
Got the signal. Give us a little time...

465
00:48:09.252 --> 00:48:11.502
<i>...and we should have his number
and location.</i>

466
00:48:12.836 --> 00:48:14.627
Your new phone, sir.

467
00:48:20.461 --> 00:48:23.461
- Anything else?
- No.

468
00:48:26.919 --> 00:48:30.669
<i>Frank, do you know where
the signal is taking you?</i>

469
00:48:41.002 --> 00:48:45.169
I know restaurant there.
Fish like you never had.

470
00:48:45.336 --> 00:48:48.502
Roasted with small carrots
and black pepper.

471
00:48:48.669 --> 00:48:51.294
Romanian wine, not so good.

472
00:48:52.836 --> 00:48:55.711
But for the last meal,
could be worse.

473
00:48:58.169 --> 00:49:01.502
You really should begin
to think more positive.

474
00:49:01.669 --> 00:49:04.044
I'm realist.

475
00:49:05.961 --> 00:49:08.669
My friend was right when he said
you were doom and gloom.

476
00:49:08.836 --> 00:49:11.711
What means "doom and gloom"?

477
00:49:11.877 --> 00:49:14.836
You know, you only see
the horrible and the terrible.

478
00:49:15.002 --> 00:49:18.002
Your friend, where does he get this?
He doesn't know me.

479
00:49:18.211 --> 00:49:21.502
He was talking about you in general.
Russians, as a people.

480
00:49:21.669 --> 00:49:23.836
I'm not Russian. I'm Ukrainian.

481
00:49:24.502 --> 00:49:25.627
Excuse me.

482
00:49:25.794 --> 00:49:29.877
Not excused. We're different people.
We're different here...

483
00:49:30.044 --> 00:49:31.252
...and here.

484
00:49:36.877 --> 00:49:40.919
Me, personally, I think there's
a little bit of an optimist in you.

485
00:49:42.461 --> 00:49:44.877
How you can make such a statement?
You don't know me.

486
00:49:46.836 --> 00:49:49.211
Well, I see you're putting makeup on.

487
00:49:49.377 --> 00:49:52.919
If you were so convinced
we was gonna die, why bother?

488
00:49:55.419 --> 00:49:58.877
What does looking good
have to do with dying?

489
00:50:05.627 --> 00:50:07.752
Hello.

490
00:50:08.711 --> 00:50:09.919
What's that?

491
00:50:10.086 --> 00:50:12.586
Souvenirs from Ibiza.
Do you want one?

492
00:50:12.836 --> 00:50:15.919
No, thank you. And neither do you.
We need to stay sharp.

493
00:50:17.961 --> 00:50:19.669
Okay.

494
00:50:24.752 --> 00:50:26.294
You stay sharp.

495
00:50:26.461 --> 00:50:29.336
I stay, how you say? Optimist?

496
00:50:29.794 --> 00:50:33.169
Give me that.
Give me that thing. Give me the pill!

497
00:50:36.461 --> 00:50:37.752
Give me that--

498
00:50:42.836 --> 00:50:45.002
Jesus.

499
00:50:47.419 --> 00:50:49.086
Great.

500
00:50:51.169 --> 00:50:54.461
- Just great.
- Come on, Frank Martin, lighten up.

501
00:50:54.627 --> 00:50:56.502
I should?
How about when those pills hit?

502
00:50:56.669 --> 00:50:59.336
You're gonna be lighting up
like a goddamn Christmas tree.

503
00:50:59.502 --> 00:51:00.627
That would be nice.

504
00:51:01.169 --> 00:51:03.669
Boring. Boring. Boring?

505
00:51:03.836 --> 00:51:05.794
Oh, yeah.

506
00:51:44.002 --> 00:51:45.794
You should stay in the car.

507
00:51:46.086 --> 00:51:48.461
You want me to pee in car?

508
