There's a dam.

763
01:20:00.462 --> 01:20:02.420
- A dam?
- I know the place, sir.

764
01:20:02.587 --> 01:20:04.420
- How far?
- Ten minutes at least.

765
01:20:04.629 --> 01:20:06.504
Frank, we'll be there in 10 minutes.

766
01:20:06.670 --> 01:20:08.004
Can you make it any faster?

767
01:20:08.420 --> 01:20:10.754
- We'll do our best.
- Thank you.

768
01:22:09.046 --> 01:22:10.587
Buy tickets for all of us.

769
01:22:11.171 --> 01:22:12.587
Where to?

770
01:22:12.754 --> 01:22:16.712
Anywhere this train is going. We need
to keep moving for half an hour.

771
01:22:16.879 --> 01:22:18.837
Why don't we just keep driving around?

772
01:22:24.462 --> 01:22:25.879
Another day.

773
01:22:40.337 --> 01:22:42.879
Sir! There!

774
01:23:00.046 --> 01:23:04.254
- Out. Out!
- Everybody out!

775
01:23:04.421 --> 01:23:05.837
- Come on.
- Move!

776
01:23:06.587 --> 01:23:08.171
Move, quick!

777
01:23:26.087 --> 01:23:27.796
- Mr. Minister?
- Yes.

778
01:23:28.379 --> 01:23:30.129
Someone wants to talk to you.

779
01:23:31.421 --> 01:23:34.129
- Papa.
- Are you all right?

780
01:23:38.671 --> 01:23:40.337
Don't sign.

781
01:23:41.004 --> 01:23:44.129
What you have is 15 minutes.

782
01:23:51.337 --> 01:23:54.087
- You ever find out what this is about?
- Garbage.

783
01:23:54.254 --> 01:23:55.837
How much garbage are we talking?

784
01:23:56.712 --> 01:24:00.337
Enough to pollute half the country
for a hundred years.

785
01:24:00.504 --> 01:24:01.504
Try it again.

786
01:24:22.171 --> 01:24:25.546
For a modern woman,
you are very uninformed.

787
01:24:25.796 --> 01:24:27.504
This is the new world.

788
01:24:28.629 --> 01:24:30.921
There are no more countries.
That's old think.

789
01:24:31.337 --> 01:24:34.712
There are just economic realities.
Profit and loss.

790
01:24:34.879 --> 01:24:37.671
Efficiency and waste.

791
01:24:37.837 --> 01:24:39.837
Think global, not local.

792
01:24:40.629 --> 01:24:42.587
Think this.

793
01:24:57.337 --> 01:24:59.337
- Yes?
- Where are we?

794
01:25:06.921 --> 01:25:08.462
We're almost there.

795
01:25:11.046 --> 01:25:12.462
Where?

796
01:25:12.629 --> 01:25:14.671
Here. He is on a train.

797
01:25:15.296 --> 01:25:17.671
- And where are we?
- Here.

798
01:25:17.837 --> 01:25:20.046
We can get units there.

799
01:25:21.671 --> 01:25:23.504
That's a good idea. Do that.

800
01:25:27.462 --> 01:25:30.337
Oh, Frank, come on.

801
01:26:02.171 --> 01:26:04.754
Mr. Minister, I assure you,
everything is in order.

802
01:26:04.921 --> 01:26:06.837
I'm sure it is.

803
01:26:07.212 --> 01:26:11.087
- If there are any problems...
- I know you will solve them.

804
01:26:12.004 --> 01:26:13.921
Now, if you don't mind...

805
01:26:44.254 --> 01:26:47.837
You might not believe this,
but I am, at heart, a pacifist.

806
01:26:49.046 --> 01:26:51.171
I hate violence.

807
01:26:53.129 --> 01:26:55.962
It creates more problems than it solves.

808
01:26:57.546 --> 01:27:00.421
You know, I never wanted to do any of this.

809
01:27:01.879 --> 01:27:05.004
A client asked me to obtain a result...

810
01:27:05.421 --> 01:27:07.546
...so I went about creating
an environment...

811
01:27:07.712 --> 01:27:09.504
...with the least amount
of bloodshed.

812
01:27:09.671 --> 01:27:12.462
No one wanted to cooperate.
Not you, not the first driver...

813
01:27:12.629 --> 01:27:16.421
...not your father, not the
recently deceased Frank Martin.

814
01:27:17.504 --> 01:27:20.129
Everyone wanted to fight.

815
01:27:35.463 --> 01:27:36.671
What's so funny?

816
01:27:37.879 --> 01:27:40.421
Hearing a dead man talking.

817
01:29:53.129 --> 01:29:55.088
One more step, Frank.

818
01:29:55.504 --> 01:29:57.046
Come on. One more.

819
01:30:40.588 --> 01:30:42.046
Look.

820
01:30:42.379 --> 01:30:43.463
It's over.

821
01:30:44.338 --> 01:30:46.004
Two minutes to 9. He signed.

822
01:30:49.796 --> 01:30:51.921
Oh, my God.

823
01:30:57.171 --> 01:30:58.629
No, Frank. No, no.

824
01:31:39.546 --> 01:31:42.004
It's over, Frank. It's over.

825
01:31:43.254 --> 01:31:45.754
Mission accomplished.
You and the girl are free to go.

826
01:31:47.338 --> 01:31:49.671
Matter of fact,
I'm so impressed by your talent...

827
01:31:49.838 --> 01:31:51.546
...I'd like to offer you a position.

828
01:31:51.713 --> 01:31:55.046
I'd like to offer you one.
Permanently disabled.

829
01:32:14.296 --> 01:32:15.671
I hate to waste talent.

830
01:32:15.838 --> 01:32:18.171
But I really don't think
we'd make a very good fit.

831
01:32:18.338 --> 01:32:19.838
That's right.

832
01:32:43.588 --> 01:32:44.713
No!

833
01:32:48.629 --> 01:32:51.838
We wouldn't fit, but you and the
bracelet were made for each other.

834
01:32:56.338 --> 01:32:57.671
No, no.

835
01:33:08.921 --> 01:33:10.004
No!

836
01:33:11.588 --> 01:33:12.838
No!

837
01:33:28.504 --> 01:33:30.421
You're doing the right thing.

838
01:33:50.213 --> 01:33:52.004
Valentina.

839
01:33:57.088 --> 01:33:58.338
Valentina.

840
01:34:08.629 --> 01:34:10.796
Am I in heaven?

841
01:34:13.879 --> 01:34:16.171
Looks more like we're in hell.

842
01:34:16.671 --> 01:34:18.504
I don't care.

843
01:34:18.796 --> 01:34:20.504
As long as we're there together.

844
01:34:32.796 --> 01:34:33.880
Yes?

845
01:34:34.046 --> 01:34:37.255
Mr. Minister,
your daughter is in good hands.

846
01:34:38.713 --> 01:34:40.338
Thank you.

847
01:34:54.838 --> 01:34:57.255
- What are you doing?
- What you said, the right thing.

848
01:34:57.421 --> 01:35:00.671
And now, if you'll excuse me,
I have a conference to address...

849
01:35:00.838 --> 01:35:03.838
...on the dangers of doing business
with people like you.

850
01:35:04.005 --> 01:35:05.005
Thank you very much.

851
01:35:24.171 --> 01:35:25.213
Is the launch ready?

852
01:35:25.380 --> 01:35:27.755
- It's on the water, sir, waiting.
- Time to leave.

853
01:35:28.463 --> 01:35:29.838
- Grab the log.
- Okay.

854
01:35:48.880 --> 01:35:51.796
I just don't understand it.

855
01:35:51.963 --> 01:35:53.963
When I was a boy, my father and I...

856
01:35:54.130 --> 01:35:57.505
...used to pull fish out of
this very spot all day long.

857
01:35:57.671 --> 01:35:59.338
Times change, inspector.

858
01:35:59.880 --> 01:36:01.671
As do people.

859
01:36:04.630 --> 01:36:06.588
You referring to me?

860
01:36:08.130 --> 01:36:10.255
I don't think that's
a very accurate statement.

861
01:36:11.171 --> 01:36:13.421
I drive the same car,
live in the same house.

862
01:36:13.588 --> 01:36:17.755
Oh, I was not referring
to your car or your house.

863
01:36:20.588 --> 01:36:23.005
The sea is so restful.

864
01:36:23.171 --> 01:36:24.338
Is lunch ready yet?

865
01:36:25.588 --> 01:36:28.921
Mademoiselle, there is
a certain progression to things.

866
01:36:29.088 --> 01:36:32.463
In order to eat the lunch,
you first have to catch the lunch.

867
01:36:32.630 --> 01:36:34.880
And if we keep talking
instead of concentrating...

868
01:36:35.046 --> 01:36:36.421
...we're gonna catch nothing.

869
01:36:36.588 --> 01:36:40.338
I have better idea. Why we
don't skip catching of lunch...

870
01:36:40.505 --> 01:36:42.505
...and go right to eating of lunch?

871
01:36:42.671 --> 01:36:45.838
I know wonderful place
just up coast from here...

872
01:36:46.005 --> 01:36:48.963
...where they make fish stew.
Incredible.

873
01:36:49.130 --> 01:36:54.921
They use tomatoes and onions,
and little amount of wild lavender.

874
01:36:55.588 --> 01:36:57.505
What kind of wine?

875
01:36:57.671 --> 01:36:59.463
Pink. From south.

876
01:37:00.713 --> 01:37:02.588
A Chteauneuf, perhaps.

877
01:37:03.005 --> 01:37:05.505
- Chilled.
- Of course, chilled.

878
01:37:05.671 --> 01:37:07.630
And for dessert?

